<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5374.1.4>
    dc:creator "Anvar, Muhammed", "Das, Sandeep", "Deepak, V.", "Gower, David J.", "Narayanan, Surya" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Rediscovery and systematics of Rhinophis fergusonianus Boulenger, 1896 (Serpentes: Uropeltidae) from India’s Western Ghats" ;
    bibo:endPage "92" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-11-15" ;
    bibo:startPage "74" ;
    bibo:volume "5374" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144989>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144991>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144993>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144995>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145005> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144989>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map showing localities for Indian species of the uropeltid snake genus Rhinophis in southwestern peninsular India. Smaller-scale map shows type localities for the six currently recognised Indian species; though note that the type locality for R. fergusonianus is the vague “Cardamom Hills”, delineated by the red frame based on Meyer et al. (1908–1931). The larger-scale, inset map shows verified localities for the four species occurring in the Nilgiri-Wayanad and Anamalai regions of the Western Ghats (see also Sampaio et al. 2020)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144991>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype (BMNH 1946.1.16.77, formerly 95.7.29.1) and previously only known specimen of Rhinophis fergusonianus. Scale bar increments 1 mm. Photographs by H. Taylor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144993>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Illustration of Rhinophis fergusonianus reproduced from Boulenger’s (1896) original description of the species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144995>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. BNHS 3687, one of the newly referred specimens of Rhinophis fergusonianus from the northern edge of the Palghat Gap. Scale bar increments 1 mm. Photographs by H. Taylor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144995/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10145005>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Maximum Likelihood (ML) phylogeny for Rhinophis. Numbers on internal branches are Bayesian posterior probability/ML bootstrap support values. See Appendix 1 for data sources. Based on analysis of data available at https://data. nhm.ac.uk/dataset/gower_fergusonianus (https://doi.org/10.5519/95s2p6kx)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10145005/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

